TeacupCMS
=========

TeacupCMS is a lightweight CMS designed to run on Google App Engine.


Installing
==========

To run TeacupCMS you need:

  * Google App Engine SDK for Python (http://code.google.com/appengine/)
  * Django (http://www.djangoproject.com)
  * google-app-engine-django (http://code.google.com/p/google-app-engine-django/)
  * django-test-extensions (http://github.com/garethr/django-test-extensions)
  * TinyMCE (http://tinymce.moxiecode.com)
  * JQuery and JQueryUI (http://jquery.com, http://jqueryui.com)


#. First install the Google App Engine SDK for Python.
#. Download and extract TeacupCMS.
#. Create `django.zip` from `django` package and place it in the `src` folder.
#. Place the `appengine_django` and `test_extensions` packages in the `src` folder.
#. Create a symbolic link to App Engine SDK in the `src` package::

    cd teacupcms/src
    ln -s ${PATH_TO_GOOGLE_APPENGINE_SDK} .google_appengine

#. Place the `tiny_mce`, `jquery.js` and `jquery-ui.js` in the `src/static/js` folder.
#. Run `python manage.py runserver` and go to `http://localhost:8000/admin/`



